AFP Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A spokesperson for the Nelson Mandela Children&rsquo;s Hospital Trust has confirmed that donations have been pouring in from wealthy donors who want to fulfil Madiba&rsquo;s dream of building a world-class paediatric hospital. According to the Sunday Times, this comes after a two-year battle by the trust to raise money to build the R1bn facility in Johannesburg.Vuyo Lutseke, the trust&rsquo;s spokesperson, said Madiba&rsquo;s death had prompted an &ldquo;outpouring of support&rdquo; by local and international donors and that R570m had already been collected.He said construction would start this month on land donated to Mandela in 2009 by the University of the Witwatersrand. &nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.